cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY. 

This paper proposes a framework for robots to perform multiple navigation tasks in indoor environments using deep imitation learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the design of a multi-headed policy to learn shared information among related tasks, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The experiments involve processing visual information, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with navigation tasks, which can be seen as a control problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
